![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/283d3ec6-4c84-42d9-ab65-52d1c39219b6/20250217_111526.jpg)

WWE superstar Seth Rollins has revealed that conversations about his potential future role in an executive or creative position within the company have begun.

In a recent interview on Bloomberg Television, Rollins shared his thoughts on his career trajectory and his growing interest in exploring opportunities beyond his in-ring work:

"I'm closer to the end of my career than the beginning, but, you know, the end ain't here yet. So, I'm kind of in my prime right now. I'm 38 years old. My mental and physical kind of, like, locked in right now where my physical hasn't declined too much, and my mental side is really on the rise, as I'm starting to see the industry from a different angle. So that part I'm really focused on."

Rollins expressed his enthusiasm for exploring new opportunities within WWE, stating:

"I think we're in the early stages of conversations about what it might look like for me in the future in an executive or in a creative role, or whatever that may be. But again, that's in its infancy."

As one of WWE's top talents, Rollins' potential transition into an executive or creative role could bring a fresh perspective to the company's leadership.